Shortcuts-Overviews:

 #1: (open command) Palette 
	strg+shift+P 
	example: open termin just type in: terminal
	can be used with other things


 #2:  Explorer Path
	strg+P
	open a file in the explorer

 #3: Toggle Sidebar
	strg+B

 #4: Select Words
	strg+D
	Change instanzes of a word -> repeat pressing strg+D (select next instance of the word)

 #5: Select all Words
	strg+shift+L
	Selects all occurencys of the word at onces

	other way to do that: Search and Replace (Find)
	strg+F

 #6: Select current Word -> better way just press strg+D onces   
 	F2 
 	Change only the current word you are on 

 #7: Open the Terminal
 	strg+shift+`

 #8: Comment out
	control+shitft+/

 #9: Get Suggestions
 	control + space
 	also use again to toggle extra information of suggestion

 #10: Fold or Unfold Block
 	control + shift + [

 #11: User Settings
	control+,


Copy Paste Lines:
 #12: 
 strg+x -> cut line
 strg+v -> paste 
 strg+c -> coppy line
 strg+shift+k -> kill line

 Move a line: 
 	alt+up or down arrow
 
 Select and copy multiple lines: 
 	alt+shift+up (or down)


 #13: Multiline (add cursore)
	Alt + Click 
		or
	strg+alt+up (or down) 
	
	strg+u (undos last cursor added)

 #14: Quick move to open files: 
 	strg+tab

 #15: Reopen last close Tabs:
 	strg+shift+T

 #16: Close all Tabs:
 	strg+W	


strg+j => toggle terminal
strg+shift+` => jump to terminal
strg+e => jump to open files


